@gunan What I said about runfiles was about same [issue faced when trying to use TensorFlow from within the source directory](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35953210/error-running-basic-tensorflow-example).
Because the `runfiles` directory has the same issue, I had to introduce [this minor hack](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/15166/files#diff-627a2a073a8f26eae4124d586f145cc5R30) to make it work.
Not ideal of course, but should be fine. If you wanna suggest a different solution, I keep an open ear.
